following is the most appropriate action for the junior doctor to take?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Seek senior supervision and assistance","Refer the patient to the respiratory team without assessment","Decline the request and ask the nurse to find another doctor","Perform the procedure with nursing staff assistance only","Attempt the procedure independently using an online guide"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eseek senior supervision and assistance\u003C/strong\u003E. This ensures patient safety while providing a learning opportunity under appropriate supervision. Junior doctors must work within their scope of practice and recognise when they need support.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are inappropriate because:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAttempt the procedure independently using an online guide\u003C/strong\u003E - This would be unsafe and outside the junior doctor\u0027s scope of practice\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecline the request and ask the nurse to find another doctor\u003C/strong\u003E - This fails to take professional responsibility for coordinating appropriate care\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERefer the patient to the respiratory team without assessment\u003C/strong\u003E - This demonstrates poor clinical handover and fails to provide immediate care planning\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPerform the procedure with nursing staff assistance only\u003C/strong\u003E - This exceeds the junior doctor\u0027s competency level and could compromise patient safety\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EJunior doctors have a professional obligation to be honest about their limitations and seek appropriate supervision. This protects patient safety while facilitating professional development through supervised learning experiences.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Junior doctors must work within their scope of practice and seek senior support when faced with situations beyond their competence.","Patient safety is paramount and requires clear communication about limitations and appropriate escalation of care.","Professional responsibility includes recognising when a task exceeds one\u0027s capabilities or experience level."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 20]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Australian Government. Unleashing the Potential of our Health Workforce \u2013 Scope of Practice Review. [online]. 2024 [Cited 2025 Jan 20]. Available at: https://www.health.gov.au/our-work/scope-of-practice-review"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65765"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18951"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65765","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65765"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-20T20:23:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-20T20:23:54+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11685"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80478"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":nul